Directions: Walk left up park road and look for flagged red maple sapling right side of road.  Turn right at flagged tree.  Plot is ~40 m from road.
Directions_updated_2024: From a huge mossy stump (or huge mound that was once a giant cottonwood tree): go 150 degrees and 9.4 meters to get to center. From a flagged 53 cm DBH silver maple: go 265 degrees and 5.43 meters.
ash_plot_centers_notes_2024: Silver maple - elm - swamp white oak - red or pin oak - Carpinus - Ilex - hickory (with a red stem) - spicebush in understory.
Center_tree_updated_2024: Center tree decomposed. Only small mossy stump remains.
